    "body": "**Summary:** \r\n\r\nWhen the location permission is denied for the app in a specific way the app screen keeps flashing with the \"Requesting Location Permission\" dialog being visible.\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce:** \r\n1. Ensure the device's location is turned off\r\n1. Use a fresh installation of the app\r\n2. Log-in to the app\r\n3. Tap on \"Nearby\". \r\n4. You'll see the location permission request\r\n5. Tap **outside** the permission dialog.\r\n6. You're shown the location permission request again (twice). Tap on \"Don't allow\" in both cases.\r\n\r\n**System logs:**\r\nLet me know if this is necessary.\r\n\r\n**Device and Android version:** \r\nOnePlus Nord running Android 11\r\n \r\n**Commons app version:** \r\n3.1.1~1c9267ca0\r\n\r\n**Screen-shots:** \r\nHere's a screen recording:\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12448084/150677090-177d9b2d-1196-4223-8b79-5dc681eda369.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**Would you like to work on the issue?**\r\nPrefer not.",
